    <div class="inner-block">
      <section class="biography" id="biography">
        <h1 class="label">Biography</h1>
        <div class="govspeak">
<p>Nick Campsie joined the Ministry of Justice as a Non-Executive Board Member on 4 June 2018.</p>

<p>He is a businessman and investor who has held senior positions in the asset management industry, including a decade as Partner of Eton Park Capital Management.</p>

<p>He was previously an Associate Director at Terra Firma Capital Partners, and an Associate at McKinsey and Company.</p>

<p>Nick supports many UK charities that provide opportunities to disadvantaged children. Nick is Chairman of Down Syndrome Education International and The Madison Foundation and Deputy Chairman of Chickenshed Theatre. He has also supported charities that address the causes of social disadvantage, including the Prisoners’ Education Trust, Breaking Barriers, and the CanDo Foundation.</p>

</div>
      </section>

      <div class="current-roles" id="current-roles">
          <section class="role_appointment role" id="role_appointment_4842">
            <h1 id="non-executive-board-member">Non-executive board member</h1>
            <div class="govspeak">
<p>Our Non-executives are senior figures from outside the department who bring a diverse mix of expertise and skills from across the public and private sector. They all:</p>

<ul>
  <li>give guidance and advice to MOJ leaders and ministers</li>
  <li>support and challenge management on the department’s strategic direction</li>
  <li>provide support in monitoring and reviewing progress</li>
</ul>
</div>
